From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] media: cedrus: h264: bound the VLD busy poll in
 cedrus_skip_bits()

cedrus_skip_bits() busy-waits on VE_H264_STATUS_VLD_BUSY with no bound.
It runs from the m2m job setup path, BEFORE the decode watchdog is
armed (cedrus_dec.c arms it only after setup() returns), so a wedged
VLD spins the CPU forever. On a single-core !PREEMPT machine (the
suniv F1C200s) that is a total silent system hang: no console, no
oops, no watchdog - observed as frequent full lockups during long
cedrus H.264 sessions on the F1C200s.

Poll with a 100 ms timeout instead. On timeout, warn (ratelimited) and
abort the skip: the frame is lost to the error/watchdog recovery path
and the machine stays alive.

Signed-off-by: mbt28 <btekbas@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_h264.c | 21 ++++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 18 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_h264.c
+++ b/drivers/staging/media/sunxi/cedrus/cedrus_h264.c
@@ -327,12 +327,26 @@
 
 	while (count < num) {
 		int tmp = min(num - count, 32);
+		u32 reg;
 
 		cedrus_write(dev, VE_H264_TRIGGER_TYPE,
 			     VE_H264_TRIGGER_TYPE_FLUSH_BITS |
 			     VE_H264_TRIGGER_TYPE_N_BITS(tmp));
-		while (cedrus_read(dev, VE_H264_STATUS) & VE_H264_STATUS_VLD_BUSY)
-			udelay(1);
+
+		/*
+		 * The VLD can wedge (observed on suniv during bring-up); an
+		 * unbounded busy-wait then silently hangs the whole machine
+		 * on !PREEMPT single-core parts, before the decode watchdog
+		 * is even armed. Give up after 100 ms instead: the frame is
+		 * lost to the error/watchdog path, the system survives.
+		 */
+		if (readl_poll_timeout(dev->base + VE_H264_STATUS, reg,
+				       !(reg & VE_H264_STATUS_VLD_BUSY),
+				       10, 100000)) {
+			dev_err_ratelimited(dev->dev,
+					    "H264 VLD stuck while skipping bits\n");
+			return;
+		}
 
 		count += tmp;
 	}
-- 
